headline: Duke Energy and its Foundation surpass $30 million over 10 years to support community resilience, disaster relief efforts
summary: As we reflect on the anniversaries of hurricanes Helene and Milton, Duke Energy Foundation announced that it, together with Duke Energy and its employees, has invested $33.8 million to nonprofit organizations since 2016 to support community resilience, emergency preparedness and disaster relief.

headline: WEC Energy Gains From Demand Growth & New Investment
summary: WEC rides the rising C&I demand and a $28 billion clean-energy plan, but faces pressure from tough competition and regulations.
